animal.description:
**NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE** ... We are so busy with rescuing and caring for animals and can't return everyone's inquiry. If you are interested in adopting this pet...You must fill out the adoption application at:
http://www.marlcares.org/adopt_app-dog.php   (cut and paste into your browser)
PLEASE READ all the following info. We do not reply to inquiries asking if the dog is still available, if it is listed here, then it is still available.

Meet ZuZu...no matter how hard we try to say "No More Room At The Inn" during the holiday...We always end up saying "Yes!" to a special dog at Christmas time...It is only fitting this precious girl be named ZuZu...because it's going to be A Wonderful Life for her as soon as she finds her happy ever after.  ZuZu came from a rural shelter in TN.  She is a typical beagle girl...loves to go exploring outside and will stay out there with nose to ground exploring and checking her yard out until she is ready to come back in.  She is kennel trained, loves a dog bed, likes other dogs, loves loves loves her treats and meals, and absolutely loves everyone she meets...she has never met a stranger.  She does love to be in a lap and does love to snuggle in the bed if you put her on the bed with you.  She is very sweet and polite and is very laid back and calm.  She was skinny and heartworm positive when we got her.  It was hard to tell how old she was, but our guess is approx 6 to 8 yrs old.  ZuZu has to have a secure fence and as you know...a beagle always needs to be on a leash when not in a fenced area because her beagle instinct tells her to go explore and smell everything out there.

$150 adoption fee, spayed/neutered, microchipped, current vaccinations, and  kennel trained.

ADOPTION APPLICATION: If you are interested in this pet you must fill out the Adoption Application…which you can find on this site or you can copy and paste this link … http://www.marlcares.org/adopt_app-dog.php
This does not obligate you in any way. If this does not work for you then you can email us at midsouthpets@aol.com for one.

PLEASE DO NOT CONTACT US BEFORE READING THE FOLLOWING INFO:  
Your inquiry may not get a reply if you have not read the info we have taken the time to provide.  PLEASE READ about our ADOPTION PROCESS AND REQUIREMENTS provided on this site before contacting us.  You can find it quickly by clicking on our NAME or MORE ABOUT US in the column to the right of this pet’s description.  All your questions can be answered by reading the following info provided below.  Our pets are fostered in the Memphis Area, a tri-state area, TN/AR/MS.  Most are fostered in Red Banks, MS.  

We do not allow meetings with any of our dogs until we have your Adoption Application.  Adopting a new family member should involve a well-thought out and deliberate process. This is not an impulse purchase. Please understand that we do not want these animals to be homeless again. We try to complete the process as quickly as possible and appreciate all the applications and will consider each and every one we receive. 

Filling out the Adoption Application does not obligate you in any way, but simply tells us a little bit about you and whether you and this pet would be a good fit for each other.  We will call you after we receive your application and answer all your questions and talk to you about this pet.  After being approved, we will set up a time to bring the pet to meet you and your family and pets or set up a time for you to meet the pet at the foster home.

NO PHONE CALLS PLEASE.  Rescue is a full time job every day.  Please know because we are so very busy with the dogs along with processing applications, updating webpage’s, rescuing, in many vet appointments, caring for seniors and hospice dogs, etc, etc that we are not able to return phone calls or emails asking if this dog is still adoptable, how much is it to adopt, is it house trained etc…We have included all the info we have on this dog at this current time and update the bio as we learn more about them.  We kennel train all the dogs and will indicate if there are housebreaking issues that we have discovered.  We update our site regularly so if the dog is listed here they are in fact adoptable, but may have applications coming in on them, so if you are interested, you need to get your application in now.

**WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO REFUSE ANY ADOPTION**  Our first concern is the happiness and welfare of the animal.  We respect our potential adoptors and appreciate your interest in adopting one of our pets.  We care about you too and that you are getting the right fit for your home and lifestyle.  By following our process, together we can make sure you are getting the right pet.**

NOTE: We prefer to adopt in the Mid-South AREA, usually no more than 1-2 hours away in driving distance. It is up to the foster home, how far they are willing to drive. We rarely adopt long distance, but will consider each and every application. 
 
MidSouth Animal Rescue League is an all breed, 501c3, non-profit organization that prefer to rescue senior dogs and special cases.  WE LOVE ROTTWEILERS...With 20 years of experience with our beloved ROTTWEILER breed, and little help for this breed in our area, we try to focus on rescuing them and try not to ever have to turn any away that need us…especially the seniors that end up in shelters.  Currently, we have several senior rottweilers in our hospice foster program.  We always need more fosters so that we never have to say NO to them or other seniors.  

We have also started a community relief effort specifically in the Red Banks, MS area not far from us, called The Dog House Project, where we go door to door providing dog houses to dogs on chains and other dogs and cats without proper shelter, including straw in cold temps, as well as food and other supplies as needed.   We offer free spay/neuter services to those animals and continue to check on them all year.  To date many have been spayed and neutered and some have been surrendered from their neglected lives on chains.  We are making a difference and need your donations to continue this program.  We always need igloo type dog houses.  

MidSouth Animal Rescue League relies on the kindness, generosity, and financial support of people like you so that we can continue to rescue and care for dogs like this one. We are a group of dedicated volunteers who respond to animals in need in shelters, strays, and from individuals. We receive no federal or state funds and are supported solely by private donations. 

Many of the animals we save are in need of special medical care or surgery to bring them back to health before they can be placed. Veterinary care, vaccinations, tests, x-rays, medications, spay and neutering, heartworm prevention, flea/tick prevention, worming, food, kennels, grooming, and other supplies are provided for each dog while in our care.

animal.description:
Rescued: 10/12/2020
Age at the time of rescue:  3 years
Current weight:  40 pounds

Trust...when we first met Pandora, she was protective of her five puppies and wouldn't let us near them at a local dumping ground. There was no way she would allow us to rescue them all that day.  A week later, we tried again and she slowly walked up to Bonnie and laid her head gently in her lap...seemingly letting trust overcome fear. What we would learn later is that there were only four puppies remaining. Life on the streets is cruel and uncertain...she took fate in her hands and changed their destiny in that moment. Once saved, Pandora showed us her sweet and playful side. She gets along with all dogs and is more on the submissive side. She's a sweetheart and we can't wait to give her the life she so richly deserves. If you'd like to apply to adopt Pandora, please log onto our website at www.scarpr.org and click on How to Adopt. Her adoption fee is $425 which includes her sterilization, vaccinations and transportation off the island of Puerto Rico. Due to flight limitation, we are only able to work with our sister shelters in the upper east coast or Minnesota. We hope to resume private adoptions in the future, thank you for your understanding and support.

animal.description: There will only be sunny skies in your future with one of the Cloudy pups at your side! Meet Look no further than this extra cute litter of Shepherd and Terrier mixes. They are around 2 months old and ready for families of their own to run, jump, and play with. We don't know who dad is or what these puppies are mixed with but they sure are cute! Their sweet mama, Cloudy, is on the medium to large side at 45 to 50 lbs. and we expect her pups to be similar in size. Stratus is looking for a family that understands the time, patience, and energy needed to raise a young pup. We require all puppy adopters to provide training that includes: house training, basic training, leash training, and socialization. Additionally, this cutie is going to need proper exercise, mental stimulation, and your attention and love to grow up to be the best companion. We do not allow our dogs or puppies to sleep or live outside; they must be incorporated into your family and be made a priority in your life. In return, you will have the most loving and loyal family member you could ask for. If you think you are ready to add to your family by adopting a puppy, then fill out an adoption application on our website today! Please note that processing time for applications is currently three to four weeks. We recommend completing the application process and connecting with a adoption coach before looking for a dog or puppy you'd like to adopt. If you're already approved to adopt or if you've adopted from Labs and More before, connect with your adoption coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Thank you for rescuing.Thank you for looking to Adopt a Labrador Retriever or other Mixed Breed Dog from California Labradors Retrievers and More Rescue. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. If you have any questions email us at doginfo@labsandmore.org or call us at 858-273-5386. Thank you for looking to a rescue group to fulfill your dream of adding a new dog to your life! Dogs + Love = Family

animal.description:
Please Note ** THIS DOG IS LOCATED IN SOUTHERN VIRGINIA. ADOPTERS MUST BE WILLING TO TRAVEL TO MEET AND ADOPT.

 C-Me is a 7 year old, spayed, female westie. She is healthy, up to date on her vaccines, and on heartworm preventive year round. 
She is sweet, outgoing, and friendly. She is crate trained, housebroken and uses a doggie door. If you have a different situation than that, she may need a little time and training to adjust.
She will need a refresher course on leash walking as she is a country dog and it has been a few years since she has needed to walk on a leash. She was shown when she was younger and was good at that time.

She has never had to climb stairs in her environment, so will need to be taught this is her new home, if needed. With time and patience, she will learn this quickly as she is very smart.
She is very cooperative for grooming, bathing ,nail trims, etc.
She will listen, but is still a terrier, and does have selective hearing at times.
She can get very bossy and will be dominant with same size female dogs. She will only tolerate them for so long then asserts herself making sure they know she is the Queen. Because of this she will NOT be adopted to a home with another female dog or ANY dog smaller than her.
We are also looking for a fenced yard.
This is NOT an apartment /condo /city dog. 
She has always lived in a quiet farm setting and has had room to run and play.
She likes her toys and loves her people. She wants to be with her people, following them around or laying on her favorite bed in the same room.
This is a referral listing to help find C-Me a great new home. Her adopter will be chosen by her owner from applicants we forward. Please contact Erica Cerny at ecerny@optonline.net or 973-361-6790 if you have interest in her or questions to see if you might be a good match for each other.  Her adoption fee is $450, and an adoption application and contract would need to be completed. East coast ONLY. 
If you have the time and love for a new best, C-me might be the westie you’ve been waiting for!

animal.description:
Friends to the Forlorn
Adopt-a-BullABOUT HARLEM

Harlem is the perfect lap dog for someone looking for a good nap companion! He loves to curl up and snuggle. For the most part, he is very laid back, but gets the zoomies every now and then - which is super cute. He loves to chase balls and is happy to lay down and chew on his kong. He does great with his harness and walks well with the leash - he loves to go on walks! He is housetrained and does well with whining at the back door when he needs to go out. We are still working on the crate training. He is easily coaxed to get in it with a treat and only barks for a few moments before settling down.

Harlem does have something known as reactive aggression with other dogs. He would need to be an only dog or a companion to someone with a very submissive dog. He does well with his foster brothers, who are very submissive, so he could be tested depending on the companion. He is easily triggered by hyperactivity and will growl/snap with toys, treats and his food. Knowing this, he would do well in a home with older kids, as he gets startled by lots of commotion and loud noises. He can also get a bit nippy when he is excited.

Harlem was an owner-surrender due to his ongoing allergies. When he came to us, his skin was red and irritated, he had eye and ear infections, and severely overgrown toenails. The skin infection has left him hairless on his chest and belly. We are treating him with medications, special diet, and weekly medicated baths - and is doing amazing. He is even already starting to show some hair growth back on his chest and belly! He will most likely need to continue allergy medication and a special diet for the remainder of his life in order to keep his skin in check.

He is also intact and has various mammary growths. He will need to be neutered once his skin clears up. The vet will also check his growths at that time to determine if they are cancerous or benign.www.savingpitbulls.org

animal.description:
Meet Sugar!

13 year old Sugar was brought in to the Orange County shelter as a stray. We got an email that this little 8 lb. cutie needed a rescue commitment quickly, so one of our volunteers went to get her on January 19th.

We vetted Sugar the next day. Our vet's first comment was that she is a very sweet girl! With a name like Sugar how could she not be? She is missing many teeth and has moderate calculus on the remaining teeth. She has two palpable mammary masses that we will be removing. She has a large mass on her left side. X-rays show that it's an abdominal hernia and her intestines are in it. The hernia is likely from a previous trauma. We will be surgically correcting this at the same time she has her mammary masses removed.

Sugar has the cutest full body wiggle when you talk to her. She acts like she wants to come over for pets and then runs away, like a "come catch me" kind of playful game. Once you catch her she loves to be held and will quickly fall asleep in your arms.

This sweet ball of sugar and spice is on a 2-week Frosted Fling! We can't wait to learn how she does in a home environment. Check back soon for an update!

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm.

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Become a family: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

Updated: 1/31/21 KG

Additionally, this cutie is going to need proper exercise, mental stimulation, and your attention and love to grow up to be the best companion. We do not allow our dogs or puppies to sleep or live outside; they must be incorporated into your family and be made a priority in your life. In return, you will have the most loving and loyal family member you could ask for. If you think you are ready to add to your family by adopting a puppy, then fill out an adoption application on our website today! Please note that processing time for applications is currently three to four weeks. We recommend completing the application process and connecting with a adoption coach before looking for a dog or puppy you'd like to adopt. If you're already approved to adopt or if you've adopted from Labs and More before, connect with your adoption coach for the next steps. Your interest in adopting a rescued dog or puppy from Labs and More Rescue is appreciated! Please find our adoption information at www.labsandmore.org. Your adoption donation provides funding for Labs and More, a nonprofit organization which is supported solely by Volunteers and funded by donations. Good news is your adoption donation can be considered tax deductible. So much care is provided to your new dog prior to the adoption, including: spay and neuter, microchip, veterinarian visit(s), vaccinations, and other medical care as needed. Many of the dogs we rescue require extensive surgeries and care prior to adoption. Please understand we are unable to predict future behavior or medical needs of your adopted dog. We provide no guarantees regarding behavior, breed, or age of the dogs. Please take a moment and go to www.labsandmore.org and click on Adopt to complete our online dog adoption application. animal.description:
NOT READY FOR HIS ROCKING CHAIR YET

Benito was a little ole guy we found down at our local shelter.  He had been brought in as a stray, with a "lady friend" who was in season.  So don't let the cloudy eyes fool ya, Benito is young at heart and still considers himself to be a ladys man.  Well, at least he did, until he was neutered.  He still likes the ladies but they will no longer lead him astray and into trouble, like they used to.

Benito is one of those, "so ugly he's cute" kind of guys and he has one of those personalities that grows on you.  Maybe even instills some respect for what he has probably lived through and how long he managed it before getting caught and sent to jail

He obviously has eye issues.  His left eye is sightless and atrophied, which makes it smaller than his other, mildly functioning eye, which while sighted, sees only shapes and shades.  The pressure in that eye is not alarming and steroid drops keep him comfortable but in all likelihood, he will be 100% blind before too long.   Not to worry though.  He has learned to compensate and even with his limited sight, enjoys exploring his surroundings and is quite confident and secure in his wanderings and adventures.  For this reason, a very secure fence will be necessary.

Benito also developed some ear polyps and had horribly abscessed teeth, all of which are scheduled to be rectified on February 12th.  His hearing, though currently compromised, is still quite functional and should improve, once the polyps are no longer obstructing his ear canals.

And that is where the medical issues end.  Everything else about this little chap is top notch.  His heart and lungs are strong and healthy and his bloodwork was excellent, so no renal issues either.  He is growing back some patchy hair loss, attributed to flea dermatitis and is just a dapper little whiskery faced guy, looking for someone to help him find his way and provide him with understanding, love and enrichment.  

Because he is an older dude and lived his life, pretty much any way he wanted to, we are not recommending a home where small children are around with any frequency.  His sight issues can cause him to react defensively and his age can cause him to grump and grouse, if he is not treated gently and respectfully.   He would love a yard he could sun himself in, in the spring and summer and explore all year round.  He loves to sit on a nice warm lap, chase the vacuum cleaner, eat soft treats and just hang out, enjoying life and living.  He is a pretty quiet guy, crates well, enjoys car rides but his potty skills require some understanding and a schedule.   He prefers to go outside but if you don't get him there, has no problem with rewarding your inattention with a clean up job.  In his foster home, they have him wear belly bands when he can't be watched and that seems to work out well.

Benito is probably at least 10 years old and more likely closer to 12+.  He is small, no more than nine inches at the shoulder, and built solid, so weighs more than it appears he should.  He has a cute little strut but walks on a leash must go slowly until he is familiar with the terrain and topography.  He is not particularly affectionate but does enjoy a good lap for napping and would appreciate the warmth of a human body at night, if his new person were so inclined.  He carries himself in the manner of a dog who has known little human affection but could learn to like it, if the bubble of his dignity can be respected.

If you would like to bring this dignified little character into your home and help his sunset chapters be filled with happy, warm, garden style adventures, please go to our website at www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and submit an adoption application. We would love to hear what inspired you to consider bringing this fella into your life and how you plan to make his life the best he's had yet.

Benito is neutered, microchipped, up to date on five way, bordatella and rabies vaccinations, is flea and parasite free and will be ready for his new home, after his dental and ear surgery on February 12, 2021

His adoption fee is $150, 

Please note:

*Inquiries submitted through Petfinder, are not the same as applications 
  submitted through our webpage.  
*Yes we do out of state adoptions.
*No, we do not transport. You must be willing to come and meet the dog and 
  take it home with you.
*Yes we do Canadian adoptions.
*If the dog is on Petfinder, it is still available.
*You must be 18 years of age to adopt
*If you submit questions about an adoptable dog, covered in the Petfinder bio, 
 we will not respond.
*We do not pick the first good application.  We pick the most suitable 
  application for the dog, out of all submitted.
*All correspondence is handled via email as time allows.  
* If you are not chosen, you will not be notified

For a more detailed explanation of our adoption process, go to www.allmuttsgreatandsmall.org/adoption and read "The Adoption Process" link

animal.description:
IF YOU WANT TO MEET FIG, FILL OUT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION ON OUR WEBSITE.
www.k94keeps.org

Fig is a sweet girl who was brought to the city shelter as a stray. 
We estimate Fig to be between 1-3 years old and a little over 50 pounds. 
Fig is well-behaved and does well on leash , but she can get excited when she sees other dogs.

Fig is becoming more confident and comfortable in her foster home, but she will need an adopter who is committed to her training. She will need special attention to her leash manners and general socialization. 

She is potty trained and will whine to let her foster mom know she needs to go outside. She is crate trained and absolutely loves her crate. She is very gentle when taking treats and doesn't mind when humans or her dog foster brother borrow her toys. 

Fig knows sit, down, paw, come and kennel. Fig is cheese motivated and would love to continue learning. Fig walks nicely on leash and shows appropriate interest and excitement when seeing other dogs. 

Fig has met one toddler and was very polite. She took treats gently and allowed for pets. She has been sweet and wiggly when meeting all different types of people. 

Fig currently lives in an apartment with another large male dog and politely greets and coexists with him. Fig doesn't seem to mind the noisy neighbors that come with living in an apartment, and the hustle and bustle of the city doesn't bother her. 

Fig loves car rides, snuggling up in  pile of blankets, taking strolls around the neighborhood and naps in the sun.

If you're looking for an independent dog that is up to go hiking but also loves to have a lazy movie marathon, Fig is your girl. Fill out an application at www.k94keeps.org to meet Figgy!

animal.description:
Fern is an adorable little Chihuahua mix who was brought to the rescue after the owner's dog had and accidental litter. We made sure mama got spayed so no more puppies would be at risk as these owners had no idea what to do with them. Fern had 3 siblings and they are all vaccinated, altered and ready for forever homes. These puppies are playful and rambunctious little characters with lots of curiosity and smarts. All are currently around 3-4 lbs at nearly 3 months and we estimate they will all be 10-12 lbs full grown. They are typical mischievous puppies that will require loads of love and thoughtful training. They have learned a great deal by spending a little extra time with their siblings as all puppies should. They are currently sleeping in a pen together at night and go outside for playtime throughout the day. They are just learning about leashes and collars but will be walking like pros in no time. The perfect home for these babies would be with another dog similar to their grown size although they can thrive without other dogs in the home. Due to their small size they would do best in a home with older children over the age of 10. 

Fern is a short coated breed who will shed some. She will require regular brushing and occasional nail trims. 

Fern's adoption fee is $325

This fee includes at least one health exam at our veterinarian while in our care, altering, all vaccinations including rabies (as permitted by age), a pre-adoption professional grooming and a microchip with lifetime membership that never will cost you a fee. 
 All dogs also leave with a new collar and or harness and leash as well as a gift bag which includes among other things, a starter bag of the quality kibble that is being fed at the rescue.
Adoption fees also allow us the ability to put funds towards the next homeless or unwanted dog in need of rescue!

If you'd like to considered to for this adoption or any of our amazing rescues, please fill our the application with the help of this link. https://www.shelterluv.com/matchme/adopt/AZST/Dog.

We review each application carefully. Please understand that sometimes we get numerous applications for particular dogs and as a volunteer based rescue we do not always have the time to respond to each and every one. We do our best to choose the most suitable home for each dog based on their specific personality and needs. 

Due to Covid, we are very short handed and may not contact you for up to a week to set up a meet and greet if your application is chosen. We appreciate all applicants and do our best to pair ever dog and family for a successful and happy life.

animal.description: Akila is our 5 year old girl and has typical husky behaviors. She is a very active dog and would do best with an active owner. She needs someone who can match her energy and keep her mind stimulated. She can’t be trusted off leash unless in a fenced area. She is currently in a foster home with other dogs but is selective about which dogs she likes, both male and female. She does not need to be in a home with small animals. She has been around older kids and did fine. She can be a bit aloof and take time to warm up to you. Once she is comfortable with you, she is very playful and affectionate. She loves tennis balls and running around and playing outside. Akila is spayed, chipped, current on vaccines and monthly prevention. For more information or to setup a meeting, e-mail adopt@mushrescue.com.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Meet Pete. He is an almost 2-year-old active, playful, happy, and curious sable and white sheltie who is affectionate and who will serenade you with music from his squeaky toys. He appears to be housetrained and walks on a leash but needs practice. Pete would do best in a home without other dogs or with a young active female dog to play with. He is a special needs pup. He has a genetic condition Dermatomyositis (DMS) which is not curable but is treatable with an inexpensive daily medication. This condition varies in severity depending on the individual dog. Best case scenario is minor, barely noticeable facial lesions and worst case is very noticeable facial lesions and muscle weakness. Pete has moderate symptoms with visible facial lesions but no indication of any muscle weakness. He runs and plays like any sheltie his age and is thankfully unaware of his condition. He has a pleasant happy expression, and we think he is beautiful despite the scars on his face. For more information on Dermatomyositis see the following links. https://www.americanshetlandsheepdogassociation.org/dermatomyositis/ Dermatomyositis studies website (This web site hasn't been updated for several years but the pictures and information is relevant) Pete will be placed with a sheltie savvy adopter who can monitor his condition and work with his or her vet if necessary. 2/1/21 6:16 PM

animal.description:
Thank you for considering a homeless/rescue dog, it does not matter where dogs are from what matters is where they will live the rest of their life. 

My name is Raina this is my story it has a sad beginning and a happy ending.  I was a stray wandering a rural neighborhood there were two very friendly ladies who helped me with my puppies.  I had two cute puppies; the nice ladies contacted a rescue group that found good homes for my family.  I was homeless for a long time, I was isolated and alienated from people, no home, no loving hands to hold me, no socialization, I am a little shy on first encounters but with a treat I will follow you anywhere, I do like people but because I am fearful, shy and timid it takes a little time to show you I enjoyed the treat and pat on the head.  The kind ladies cared for me providing food and water where I felt safe at an abandoned house is where I laid my head at night.  They were very patient trying to befriend me, over time I felt comfortable enough for a belly rub and a hug.  I was then, saved.

This is my story; I am Raina’s foster mom.
I am a volunteer foster mom with Paws & Claws Rescue, Raina came into my care on October 26, 2020 today she is a different dog very sweet, loving, affectionate and completely trusting.  She loves a serious belly rub; she jumps up for a hug.  Only a few weeks ago she would not walk with a harness and lead, now she enjoys her walks, runs back to me for a treat after each time she relieves herself, a 100% progress.  She is crate trained sleeps in her large wire crate at night & potty trained, she’s very smart and learns quickly, she sits for her treat and food this progress she has learned this in my care, again, she learns quickly. 

Raina is ready to join a quiet loving patient family, she’s the full package a sincere sweet personality, sweet natured, frisky she likes to run and play, likes everyone she meets but will be timid & shy upon first encounters to new people. 

Raina is 60 pounds of love; she was thin now she’s fit and sassy. Raina is  Anatolian Shepherd/Great Pyrenees mix?  It is difficult to identify mixed breed dogs without proper knowledge of ancestry; a guess assessment of breed and age has been made. Both breeds are basically considered good family pets, loyal, devoted and true to their family. 

Raina is approximately 2 years old still very young she enjoys sitting on her dog house when outdoors. She is waiting for someone to make her dream come true with toys of her own, big comfy bed, and a home with a family that will shower her with love and attention. Raina has loving eyes that invite you in with a pleading expression “please open your heart and home give her a chance to prove her love”.

She needs a family who will love, walk, play and care for her.  She needs a forever home where she can hang her leash and call “Home, Sweet Home”. Raina will enjoy a quiet home. I am looking for a nice fenced yard where she can run and play.  Again, an extremely patient family showing much dedication to help with Raina’s progress.  The process maybe slow but the out-come is gaining her love and trust.  Raina loves to walk we walk in the woods on a path where she can enjoy all the different smells and odors of the woods.  We do not walk on city streets vehicle noise may make her nervous and anxious?  Raina walks by my side, no pulling or tugging she is a great walking partner.  It’s important to have a supply of tasty treats on our walk, Raina sits without a command, she loves her treats.      

Raina’s adoption donation is $150.00 which includes all her expenses and vetting, etc.  She is current on vaccinations; monthly flea & tick & heartworm preventative. She has been micro chipped and spayed ready for her new home. If you would like additional information and an adoption application, please contact his foster mom Delia at rubsch@sbcglobal.net and please include your phone number.  

Rescue dogs form a lifelong bond with their families and are forever grateful for their new happy family and life. Our rescue dogs come in all shapes, colors and sizes they love unconditionally.

animal.description:
CROSBY IS A BIG SWEET DOG THAT HAS BEEN LEFT TO ROAM TO TAKE CARE OF HIMSELF FOR AWHILE.HE HAD A FAMILY BUT HE WAS ALLOWED TO COME AND GO AS HE PLEASED. HE WAS ALWAYS FRIENDLY WITH NEW PEOPLE AND HE MET PLENTY OBN HIS TRAVELS AROUND HIS NEIGHBORHOOD. PROBLEM IS, NO ONE KNEW WHERE HIS HOME WAS & WHEN HE ENDED UP IN OUR RESCUE AS A STRAY WE WERE ABLE TO FIND HIS OWNER AND RETURN HIM. AFTER A COUPLE OF WEEKS HE WAS PICKED UP AS A STRAY AGAIN & OUR RESCUE WAS CALLED. THIS TIME HIS OWNER AGREED TO SURRENDER HIM SO HE COULD FIND A HOME AND BE PART OF A FAMILY FOR REAL THIS TIME. AND THAT'S ALL CROSBY WANTS...A FAMILY...SOME LOVE....SOME TREATS...SOME NAPS....SOME PLAY TIME...AND SOME PATIENCE& SOME UNDERSTANDING. CROSBY HAS TURNED INTO A REAL PET WHILE IN FOSTER CARE. HE LIKES THE ROUTINE AND THE SECURITY. HE IS SELECTIVE ABOUT WHO HIS FRIENDS ARE AND DOESN;T TAKE TO JUST ANY OLD DOG THAT WANTS TO BE BUDDIES. 
CROSBY WANTS A HOME TO CALL HIS OWN. HE WANTS CONSISTANT LOVE AND ATTENTION. NOT CONSTANT! JUST SOMEONE HE CAN COUNT ON. HE HAS GOTTIN BETTER ON A LEASH AND WILL ONLY PULL WHEN FIRST GETTING OUT OF HIS KENNEL AND BEING WALKED OUTSIDE. HE GETS PRETTY EXCITED TO GO OUT AND PEE WHEN HE WAKES UP. THEN HE WILL CALM DOWN. A FENCED IN YARD WOULD MAKE EVEYONES LIFE EASIER BUT IT'S NOT MANDATORY. HE LIKES TOYS AND HE WILL GET AROUND TO TEARING THEM UP JUST LIKE ANY GOOFY DOG WILL DO, BUT HE'S NOT DESTRUCTIVE. HE HAS NOT BEEN AROUND CHILDREN AND HAS NOT BEEN TESTED WITH THEM. HE HAS NOT BEEN TESTED WITH CATS. 
CROSBY IS NEUTERED, UP TO DATE ON VACCINES AND HEART WORM NEGATIVE. HE IS MICROCHIPPED.LOCATED IN CROSSVILLE, CUMBERLAND COUNTY, TN. WE CAN TRANSPORT OUT OF STATE

animal.description: CAM IS A BIG ATTENTION SEEKING SWEET GOOFBALL OF A BABY. HE HAS SPENT HIS 4.5 YEARS LIVING ALMOST ENTIRELY OUTSIDE OFTEN TIED TO A TREE. OBVIOUSLY THIS IS HARD ON A DOGS PSYCHE AND LIKE MOST DOGS THAT ARE HOUSED FAR AWAY FROM THEIR ""FAMILY"" CAM CRAVES THE ATTENTION HE HAS BEEN DENIED.HE IS VERY EXCITED & HAPPY TO BE GETTING DAILY LOVE AND AFFECTION AT HIS FOSTER HOME. HE HAS A VERY TYPICAL GREAT DANE PERSONALITY...AFFECTIONATE AND SWEET;HE TRIES TO BACK UP AND SITON YOUR LAP;HE PUTS HIS FRONT P ON YOUR LAP AND STANDS ON HIS BACK FEET AND TOWERS OVER YOU TO BE PETTED; AND HE STANDS NEXT TO YOU AND LEANS. HE NEEDS SOME TRAINING BUT HE IS HIGHLY FOOD MOTIVATED AND REALLY WANTS TO PLEASE. THERE WERE OUTSIDE CATS AT HIS PREVIOUS HOME AND THEY WOULD OFTEN COME CLOSE AND WE WERE TOLD HE NEVER OFFERED TO BOTHER ANY OF THEM. THERE WERE ALSO YOUNG CHILDREN IN THE HOUSE AND HE WOULDN'T DARE HURT ONE ON PURPOSE. HOWEVER HE HAS NO IDEA OF HIS SIZE AND CAN BE A JUMPER WHEN HE IS EXCITED TO SEE YOU. HIS FOSTER FEELS LIKE HE WOULD DO BEST IF ANY CHILDREN IN THE HOME WHERE OLDER. CAM IS NOT LEASH TRAINED AND IS DIFFICULT TO WALK. HE CAN BE TAUGHT OF COURSE WITH A GENTLE LEADER HARNESS AND SOME TIME AND TREATS. BUT WE FEEL CAM WOULD BEST BE PLACED IN A HOME WITH A TALL FENCE. HE NEEDS TO PLAY OFF LEASH TO BURN OFF ENERGY. A TIRED GREAT DANE IS A GOOD GREAT DANE. CAM DOES WELL INSIDE. HE HAS TAKEN TO HIS KENNEL (IT'S A 5'X5' WALK IN KENNEL). HE HAS ALSO TAKEN TO HIS ELEVATED BED BUT RECENTLY TORE APART A FIBER FILLED BLANKET THAT WAS PUT ON HIS BED IN HIS KENNEL. HIS FOSTER DOESN'T REALLY BLAME HIM. HE WAS LEFT IN THE KENNEL TOO LONG WITH NO ENRICHMENT TOYS TO OCCUPY HIM AND PROBABLY GOT BORED. CAM WON'T BE THE EASIEST DOG AT FIRST. HE NEEDS TO LEARN SOME MANNERS. BUTHE COULD TEACH CLASSES ON HOW SWEET AND FUNNY A DOG CAN BE AND HE IS SO WORTH THE TIME AND EFFFORT TO TRAIN HIM. HE SEEMS TO BE KENNEL TRAINED AS LONG AS HE ISN'T LEFT IN THE KENNEL TOO LONG WITHOUT BEING LET OUT. HIS FOSTER THINKS HE WOULD DO GREAT IN A HOME WHERE HE COULD LEARN TO GO TO THE DOOR TO BE LET OUT.CAM IS HOUSED WITH MANY DOGS AT HIS FOSTER HOME. HE HAS ONLY HAD A PROMBLEM WITH ONE OTHER MALE WHO WAS NOT YET ALTERED. HE HAS BEEN AROUND SMALL DOGS LARGE DOGS MEDIUM SIZED DOGS AND PUPPIES.CAM IS NEUTERED UP TO DATE ON VACCINES AND MICROCHIPPED. HE IS HEART WORM NEGATIVE AND ON PREVENTION.LOCATED IN CROSSVILLE, CUMBERLAND COUNTY, TN. WE CAN TRANSPORT OUT OF STATE

animal.description:
In FosterHi, my name is Sampson. I am one tough little guy. While I was with my previous owner, I got hit by a car and my injury was pretty severe. I have been with my current foster since November and we have slowly nursed me back to health despite many setbacks. I went through lots of painful surgeries and nearly lost my leg. However, I am a fighter and today I am doing great and running like a champ. I have spent a lot of down time healing so now that I can run, I have a lot of energy. I love to have your full attention. I am the sweetest boy and get along well with my fosters other 2 dogs. I have been around lots of people as my foster has a home salon and I have been the welcoming committee.

My ideal family is one that will allow me to be part of the family and not just an outside dog. I have never had an accident inside, I am crate trained but don't require one. I love to eat and have gained my COVID 15 lbs. I was painfully thin for a long time.

I would make a great addition to a home with or without another pet. Please consider me for your family as I deserve the best life. I promise I would give all of the love and kisses you could handle. If you are interested in adopting Sampson, please fill out an application at royalanimalrefuge.org/adopt <3

OUR ADOPTION PROCESS AND APPLICATION IS AVAILABLE AT WWW.SOHODOGRESCUE.ORG AND OUR ADOPTION FEE IS $275

Bella is a very sweet puppy who is ready for her forever home.  She is a Border Collie/Great Pyrenees mix, she is 5 months old and she weighs 35 pounds.  Bella has a full black and white coat with super cute freckles and a full tail.  She is housebroken and crate-trained.  Bella is a very smart little girl and she is quickly learning her basic obedience commands.  She rides pretty well in the car and she is making progress walking on leash with the help of a harness.
Bella loves people and is a joy to be around.  She is a higher energy, higher Velcro dog who loves to play and then settles nicely when playtime is over!  Bella also loves other dogs, and she loves a good game of chase or tug of war with her dog pal.  Bella is a cat-chaser.
The ideal home for Bella is one that includes an active, fun-loving family who is ready for a fun and funny young girl.  A fenced yard and another playful young dog are important, children over the age of 10 are welcome, and no cats please.  It is also important that Bella’s family commit to continue her training – she has amazing potential.  If Bella is a great match for you, apply today!  Bella is fostered in Clarksville, TN.

Hanna is a sweet shepherd/lab mix that was rescued from out of country.  She is only 7 months old and weighs about 40 lbs.  

She is very shy and timid but not aggressive.  She does not walk on leash yet, she gets scared and freezes up.  We are sure she can learn with time and patience, best suited for someone that has a yard to work with her.

She loves to play with toys but doesn't want to share them with other dogs.  With people, she plays nice with toys. She is OK with children 8 years and older. 

Hanna is learning how to give kisses, loves her food and will do anything for treats! She is not a barker, is house trained and knows how to use a doggie door.  She has been to the dog park and does very well running around with her friends.

She is spayed, up-to-date on shots and microchipped.  If you are interested in Hanna, please complete the on-line application that can be found on our website: www.adoptmerescue.org or contact us for more information.

animal.description:
In Foster/ 14 yrs old

Hi friends, my name is Jasmine! I am the newest resident at RAR. I want to share my story with you.

My mom was tragically murdered days ago. I have lost everything I have ever known. For the past 14 years, I have woken up next to my best friends, and now they are gone. I had a teenager best friend, but her world has now changed too and we were not able to stay together. I am heartbroken and grieving at a new place with so many new things that are so unfamiliar to me. This is
very hard. I can still get around pretty well, but at my age, I am just looking for a soft spot to land and could give me some pets. I would prefer to be the only child, but that's because that's how I have lived my entire life. Before I forget, my new friends here did tell me to hold tight that someone would be coming for me, but we have to get through some medical issues too. I was taken to the vet to do a full work up and the vet said that my bladder looks abnormal. I am on antibiotics in hopes that this is an infection that I can get through, but I do have a follow up in a week to see if I have improved. My next foster or adoptive family has to be okay with driving me to my appointments to ensure I am medically taken care of. I know it is a lot to ask for, but I have lost everything and need a purpose to continue living. Could you share this post to help me?

With love,
Jasmine

If you wish to donate towards Jasmine's medical care, please do so below. Any amount helps! If you are unable to donate, please share or comment on this post, even if it is an emoji. It will create more reach for Jasmine. We genuinely appreciate anything you can do.



To adopt please visit royalanimalrefuge.org/adopt

To foster please visit royalanimalrefuge.org/foster

It's hard to believe no one has scooped up our sweet wiggly Jax Jax is a happy go lucky boy, goofy as he can be, loyal and loves to please his people. He's successfully completed his board and train and is now ready to start his next chapter in a home like setting! It really is past this pup's turn to find either his forever family or a foster family that's ready to continue to work with him and

continue to show him the ropes of what life and love is all about!

The perfect candidate for Jax would be an experienced dog handler. A decent sized fenced in backyard, older kids 12+ years old and a person that is dedicated to his continual training. If another dogs lives in the household it would need to be a female and of similar size, 50lb+.

A huge shout out to Integrated K9 Solutions for spending so much time working with, loving on and setting Jax up for success.

If you are interested in adopting or fostering Jax, please submit an application:

Adopt:
royalanimalrefuge.org/
adopt

Foster:
royalanimalrefuge.org/
foster

Introducing Jax! Those sweet eyes are killing us... Without even saying a word, you can just tell this sweet boy is desperately ready to be in a home! Jax has successfully completed his board and train and is now longing for his forever or even simply a foster family to come and sweep him up!

The perfect candidate for Jax would be an experienced dog handler; examples would be Doberman pincher German Shepherd, Mal, Pitbull type dog. A decent sized fenced in backyard, older kids 12+ years old and a person that is dedicated to his continual training. He will need a owner that is firm but fair and understands how to correct that behavior and redirect it into a positive situation. If another dog lives in the household it would need to be a opposite sex (female) and of some what of similar size.

animal.description:
Skye is ready to go!

But, only if you think you can keep up with her.

You see Australian Shepherds have incredible endurance and are extremely intelligent by nature.

They require keeping both their bodies and minds challenged in order to be content.

And, Skye is no exception to the rule.

She would benefit from having a shared activity with you such as Agility Training, Trick Training, Hiking, Nose work, Frisbee and more!

Skye has already learned some basic obedience and would like a home where she can continue to learn.

She is up to any task and in fact she would love to have a regular "job" to do.

Skye is also very sweet, loves affection and just being close to her favorite people.

If you spend more time off of the couch than on it and are ready for endless active pursuits fill out an application form for Skye today!

ADOPT ME ONLINE: https://ophrescue.org/dogs/8515

Hi! I'm Remembering Avi. 

I may be 70lbs but Im the sweetest pup youll ever meet. Im a little over a year old and Im fully house/crate trained. I love to cuddle and be close to my human. Im not sure why they always say ouch or move over when I sit in their laps. I love kids, other dogs, bones, and being outside. I have quite a loud bark that I use often to protect the house from any noises. I know basic commands and Im trying to learn that when my humans eat I should give them space. I enjoy my fur foster sibling but I dont like when she comes close to my food or bone. 

Here are some snazzy things about me my foster family thinks you should know:
- housebroken
- crate trained
- knows basic commands
- good with other dogs
- good with cats
- good with children
- likes to play a lot
- loves walking
To adopt this dog, or any OPH dog, fill out the simple online application at https://ophrescue.org 
Operation Paws for Homes, Inc. (OPH) rescues dogs of all breeds and ages from high-kill shelters in NC, VA, MD, and SC, reducing the numbers being euthanized. With limited resources, the shelters are forced to put down 50-90% of the animals that come in the front door. OPH provides pet adoption services to families located in VA, DC, MD, PA and neighboring states. OPH is a 501(c)(3) organization and is 100% donor funded. OPH does not operate a shelter or have a physical location. We rely on foster families who open their homes to give love and attention to each dog before finding a forever home.

animal.description:
Lili / Female / 12 Years / 42 lbs / Street Mix / Toronto

Meet Lili! Lili spent almost 10 years in a shelter, waiting for a family to choose her. Black dogs all over the world are often overlooked, and unfortunately Lili fell victim to this stigma. When our partner shelter in Mexico saw a publication detailing her story, they immediately went to get her out. They knew if she was given the chance - she would make an excellent addition to a lucky family. Once she was cleared to travel, she made the long trip to Canada. Lili is so deserving of a special family who will support and love her through her senior years!

Lili is described as spunky, confident, curious, smart, affectionate, energetic and highly trainable. They say you can’t teach an old dog new tricks but Lili proves this is FALSE. She is clearly making up for lost time and lives every single day to its fullest. She can be a little bossy and demanding at times but she is responsive to leadership. She is always ready for belly rubs, food and lives for puzzles toys. She keeps surprising her foster family with her youthful zest for life!

Lili is a social dog but she needs proper introductions with people. She has met people in her building and in the hallways and she will generally just sniff or maintain a respectful distance. When meeting people in a stressful situation (like the vet) she may bark or snap. She is much more weary of men and may take a few days to warm up to them. Once she is given adequate time to learn proper greetings and social skills, she will likely do fine.

Lili is still adjusting to life as a pet and living inside a home. She needs boundaries and structure to understand humans expectations of her. Her adoptive family will have to invest time in her training to bring out the best in her. She is trusted with free reign of the home but she is crated at night time. Granted she receives enough opportunities to use the washroom, she is fully potty-trained.

Lili loves her walks and will need approximately 4 shorter walks throughout the day. She can be reactive to other dogs on leash and will bark and/or lunge. Given her size she can only be walked by a very strong handler. Adopters should be confident in their ability to redirect her as needed. She is highly food motivated so treats being on hand will be essential to her success. She is smart and has already learned sit, relax, wait and come!

Lili’s ideal family would have some dog experience and understand the importance of setting boundaries for her. She doesn’t like the company of other dogs so far, so she would need to be the only pet in the home. She will need adopters who are home more often than not and can support her through some mild seperation anxiety. Although she can adapt to most living environments, Lili would be happiest in a house with fully fenced backyard. She would love the opportunity to run, sniff and explore in the safety of a secure area. Lili is only looking for homes with children that are 14+.

If you’re interested in adopting Lili please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Lili’s adoption fee is $420. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

animal.description:
Snapshot of Joy!

Size?
I'm still growing, but I bet I'll be a medium/large pup!

Age?

6 months

Activity Level?
I play hard and snuggle hard!

Noise Level?
No shared walls, please.

Good with Dogs?
I would LOVE a playmate!

Good with Cats?
No cats, please!

Good with Kids?
Older kids only, if you please!

Good with Strangers?
I bark at first, but warm up quickly!

Potty Trained?
I'm a pro!

Crate Trained?

I would prefer not to be crated but with some more training I'm sure I could learn to like a crate!

Interested? Learn more about Joy below!

About Joy:

Hi! My name is Joy and I am a young Catahoula mix! I traveled all the way from TX to MN with my sister in search of my forever home. You would never know that I wasn't from MN though with how much I love running in the snow! I could play in it forever if it didn't cause my little paws to get cold.

I currently live in a very busy house with other dogs, some cats, a few adult humans, and a couple baby humans. After taking a little bit of time to adjust, I decided that I love to have other dogs in the house! They keep me company and will play with me! I'm still learning about cats. I think I would prefer to have only dogs in my forever home though. I do fine with the little kids as well. I can be very gentle if I want to be. But sometimes I get really excited about things which can be a bit overwhelming for the littles. I think I would do best with slightly older kids that are comfortable with walking. I loooove the adults though! They give me pets and treats and toys and treats. Did I mention treats? I am super food motivated if you can't tell (:

I have a lot of energy, but it's manageable! Right now I tire myself out by running around on an extra-long leash through the snow, chasing squeaky toys that my foster mom throws, or playing with puzzle toys. If I had a fenced yard that would be even better! Once I'm tired out, I like to snuggle up with whoever is around! I'm really good at finding a spot next to you on the couch, on your lap if there's minimal space, or even on your shoulder at the top of the couch if needed! I don't mind snoozing by myself on a soft surface either if all of the humans are busy.

I've been through a lot of big changes in my short life that have caused me to have some anxiety when my people aren't right by me. I think my human's call is separation anxiety? But they give me meds twice a day and it really helps me chill out. Since I'm so young there's a good chance that I will be able to get off of the meds when I'm settled into my forever home. But for right now they are really helping me become comfortable in new places. Some other things that help me are having another confident dog around and not being in a kennel. I really enjoy sleeping with my people at night and would love it if my forever family was comfortable with that too!

I'm listed as *foster to adopt* because I would love to get into my forever home as soon as possible, but I still need to by spayed :) I'm looking for a family that is willing to bring me to my spay appointment on Jan 28th in Minneapolis, and show me lots of love until I'm cleared for full adoption with you!

Adoption Fee: $475*

*I have a discounted adoption fee so my forever family can invest in training with me to help me with my separation anxiety, and continue with my medications until I'm feeling fully settled with you!

Training Requirement: Obedience Level 1

MEET ME/ADOPT ME: If you'd like to arrange a meeting or begin the adoption process, please fill out an adoption application by visiting www.twincitiespetrescue.org/adopt/adopt-a-dog/ . A volunteer from Twin Cities Pet Rescue will contact you once your application is reviewed.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED!!! Twin Cities Pet Rescue is a volunteer-run, foster home-based organization. We can only rescue as many animals as available foster homes. Please consider saving the life of an animal in need and become a volunteer foster home today. To become a foster, fill out a dog or cat foster application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.twincitiespetrescue.org . There is little to no cost to foster an animal. Twin Cities Pet Rescue provides its foster families with food, supplies, and veterinary care for its animals. All you need to do is supply the love!

PLEASE NOTE: Twin Cities Pet Rescue does not adopt to homes further than 60 miles from the Minneapolis/St. Paul Metro Area.

She kennels well, cries a bit at the beginning when she sees she is by herself but now that she's figured out we will be back she gets over it after a few minutes. She needs help working on potty training however she is doing really good from where she was the first couple of days! She loves to eat snow, her first snow experience was too funny as she didn't know what it was, she gets chilly after 6-8 minutes outside so you need to walk with her to make sure she goes potty. On sunny days she'll stay outside a bit longer and will play with our dog, she loves to run around the yard chasing her and she is fast!

She is great with our 7 year old and with other dogs, she might get a bit possessive with food and treats so it is important to feed them separately.

Gigi needs a family with lots of love to give, will be important to have patience with her and let her adjust and come out of her shell, she loves belly rubs and to hear she's a good girl!

animal.description:
*PLEASE NOTE: WE ARE REQUIRING ARCTIC'S FOREVER HOME HAS SIMILAR BREED EXPERIENCE, A YARD, AND ANOTHER DOG*

Arctic is a 1 year old neutered male Great Pyrenees who weighs 70 lbs, though he is quite thin and needs to gain weight. Arctic was rescued from death row after being dumped at a high kill shelter in Georgia. This beautiful boy is so sweet despite everything he's been through. He loves when you pet his fluffy coat and scratch behind his ears. He gives the best hugs too! Arctic has been doing very well in his foster home and is slowly gaining some much needed weight. He has been good with other dogs he has met and really seems to gain confidence from being around other dogs, so he is looking for a home with a canine sibling or two. Arctic has even done well with his dog-savvy foster kiddos, but unfortunately, he'll need a home without cats. Arctic will need a forever family that is familiar with guardian breeds and a large yard for him to stretch his legs and patrol. We adore this fluffy marshmallow and have promised him the loving forever family he deserves... could it be yours??

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description: Notes from our volunteer: Grayson is an absolute dreamboat. He exudes happiness and has the biggest, most slobbery smile. Grayson has excellent doggy manners. He gets excited sometimes (zoomies!) but is very respectful and quickly calms down if asked. He knows sit and shake. He takes treats ever so gently and is food motivated. Grayson seems to have a medium energy level; he is easy to walk on leash and enjoys exploring. He also loves to just hang out. He will gladly jump up beside you and attempt to sit in your lap - more scritches please! Grayson can be a bit shy with strangers and it will probably take a new family a couple of visits with Grayson for him to relax and feel comfortable. Patience and TLC will be key! If you're looking for an easy, fun and loving dog to put a smile on your face, Grayson is your guy!

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN TREVOR, YOU MUST FILL OUT AN APPLICATION AT BFPA.ORG. APPLICATIONS ARE PROCESSED IN THE ORDER THEY ARE RECEIVED.

Foster comments:

Meet Trevor a 7 month old hound mix puppy. He is currently @30 pounds and can potentially be @60 pound. Trevor is very friendly and is always excited to see other dogs on walks. He has not been around cats and has lived in a home with a child and they got along very well. He is looking for an active family who wants to go on lots of walks/hikes/runs with him. He is a puppy and deserves a family that has time for him.

Trevor is a quiet dog, I have only heard him bark once, and he is housebroken! He goes out to the bathroom every 3-5 hours. Trevor sleeps great in his crate through the night with no accidents.

Trevor has alot of puppy energy! After a 30-45 minute walk, he is ready to play for an hour. He needs to go to a family who will take him on several walks a day or go on runs and play with him after. A fenced yard is a must! A family with a child(ren) who will want to run around with him or a family with a young dog that likes to play could be a good fit for getting that energy out.

Trevor loves to go on walks and explore. He is a puppy but he walks good on the leash and gets better every day. In addition to loving walks, he loves to play fetch, play with his toys and chase/watch squirrels.

Trevor is very smart and has learns really fast. He has learned the command 'sit' and we are working on 'down'. He has also learned not to go up the stairs or inside the house before the person with him.

If your family has the time for a puppy, Trevor could be a good fit. He is very sweet, loving and a playful dog. He is looking for an active family who is not gone for 8 hours a day. After he gets his wiggles out, he is very calm and super cuddly and sweet. He will grow into a wonderful companion.

EVERY DOG HAS A STORY: Trevor was found as a stray, all alone. He was taken to a rural shelter and BFPA is now looking for his forever home.

INTERESTED IN ADOPTING TREVOR? If so, please fill out our dog adoption application by copying and pasting this link in a new browser window:
https://toolkit.rescuegroups.org/of/f?c=WHMSYCNC

animal.description:
Welcome Bullet to CCPAL Rescue.  He is a 3-year-old Plot Hound mix that weighs about 75 lbs.  He is a little on the timid side and would be best with another dog for company.  He is a real home body and was raised spending most time in the back yard when his family works.  He spends it with another dog.  He would do best with kiddos 8 or older and another dog.  I think a family that is more of a home body family that wants a dog to match this lifestyle would be best.  He is in Texas and can be adopted locally or we can work with the wonderful transporters to deliver him to Washington, Portland, Minnesota, Wisconsin, Vermont or all along the East Coast.  His adoption fee it is 250 and transport is 185.  Rhode Island and Massachusetts are not states we adopt to because of the regulations imposed by these states. 

Contact Marlene at 210-867-1769 or email to ccpalinquiries@gmail.com if you have questions. Online applications at www.ccpal.info/ See his cute video!!

Lucky will thrive in his forever home and be your faithful companion. He will be responsive to positive reinforcement training. Our experienced staff is available to talk with you, answer your questions and provide advice on how to transition him to your home.
Lucky is neutered, dewormed, treated to prevent fleas & ticks and is up to date with vaccinations. His adoption fee is $350 plus $8.50 for the dog license if you are a resident of NYC, and he'll get one free exam at our vet's office, and a microchip. If you'd like to adopt him please call or visit...we are conveniently located in Windsor Terrace, Brooklyn near the F train and we're open every day from 11am to 7pm.

Say hello to the very cute, very sweet Travis. Travis is estimated to be about 11 months old and weighs 41 pounds. He came to the shelter as a lost boy on 01/13 and has not been found. Travis is a playful fellow and loves toys. He is still young and eager to please and will make a great student so that you can teach him all you want him to know. He already sits when told. A home with a back yard to romp in and then a nice soft bed at your feet would be perfect. Travis is current on his vaccines, now neutered, heartworm tested negative and will be micro-chipped upon adoption. He is waiting to meet you in run 826 and his ID# is 626854.

Please note, all of the pet listings on Friends of Shelter Animals for Cobb are done by volunteers, not shelter staff. If this pet came in as lost (not an owner surrender), we don't know how they might be with children, other pets, or if house trained. You can bring your pet to the shelter for a meet & greet with your potential new best friend. When calling the shelter about a cat or dog, please use THE ID NUMBER, names are oftentimes made up by volunteers. 

This pet and many others are available for adoption from the Cobb County Animal Shelter 1060 Al Bishop Dr. Marietta, GA 30008, call (770) 499-4136 for more information. Shelter hours are: Tues. - Sun. 10:30 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. by appointment only until further notice, CLOSED Mondays & Holidays.

animal.description:
Nelson is endearing with his great smile and happy, goofy personality.  Like his brother Diego, he was found at the southwest landfill and is now looking for a permanent home.  He is super friendly and happy to do anything with people.  He is about one year old, mixed breeds of German Shepherd and maybe Malinios, and weighs about 60 pounds.  He walks like a dream on leash, but will need to learn some house manners.  He will likely get along with a playful female dog, or his brother Diego.  They can, but don’t have to be, adopted together.  It is likely cats may not be compatible, and children that are over 10 may be best due to Nelson’s energetic nature.  Nelson would enjoy having a walk or hike daily and some playtime.

animal.description:
??ADOPT PESO??
Hi all, I’m Peso, an approximately 13 year old Chihuahua who was adopted from us back in 2017 & spent the past 3 years being the cherished companion of an elderly woman. I loved being a spoiled lapdog. Sadly, my mom passed away last month & family was unable to take me in. They reached out to HFD & I’m so glad my former foster home was able to welcome me back with open arms. 

I am around 10 pounds, housebroken, neutered, vaccinated, microchipped & heartworm negative. I’m fostered with other dogs & cats & I co-exist with them just fine, I just like my space. I would have no problem being an only pet as I love being spoiled by people. I’m not interested in playing with other dogs. My favorite place to sleep is right next to my foster mom & I love burrowing under covers or couch blankets. Being a man of a certain age, I’m set in my ways so if other animals get in my face I’m snappy. But I’m all talk to be honest, & also have almost no teeth left anyways. (HFD did a full dental with extractions back in 2017 because my teeth were so terrible.) But to be safe my foster mom is recommending a home without kids. 

Although I have pep in my step I’m not overly yappy & I really love to just snooze next to you. Most of all, I just want to go somewhere where I can stay forever with someone that loves & understands Chihuahuas. I have a special senior adoption fee of $150. For further information please email my foster mom at amandarescues78@gmail.com or head over to www.heathersfosterdogs.com to download & submit an application online.

(I am fostered in the south suburbs of Chicago & after your application is submitted we can set up a Covid-safe meet & greet.)

animal.description:
Mae is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet her.

Mae is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~1.5 years 
Weight: ~41lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! She needs to be on a strict schedule 
Crate trained: Working on it! She takes some time to settle (10-30 minutes) and will benefit from continued training for this
Dog sociability: Mae tested well with dogs at her prior shelter, but while in foster she has shown leash reactivity (barks/lunges at other dogs). She may be a bit selective of her dog pals and may do better with slower intros off-leash.
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Friendly with kids
Ideal home: Mae will do well in a quieter neighborhood where she can really work on her leash skills! She would love to get into training and have lots of awesome enrichment as she undergoes her heartworm treatment the next ~9 months. She is not a match for a high-rise/elevator building due to her leash reactivity. 

If you're looking for a loyal, fun loving sweetheart, Mae is your gal. This girl has so much love to give and is always looking for ways to comfort and please. When she starts to feel at home, she'll start playing with her stuffy toys and is so cute while she chases them, squeaks them, or falls asleep on her toys. You can tell this girl loves fetch, she brings all of her toys back to her person and asks for them to be thrown again. She loves sniffing around and exploring the outdoors, looking up at you to make sure you have her back. She's so smart and realized so quickly that her crate is her safe den and has learned to sit by the door when she needs to go potty. Most importantly, she loves snuggles. She'll come up to you and bury her head by your shoulder to get affection and comfort. 

Mae is heartworm positive and will be undergoing treatment at our Ellis Veterinary Clinic. OTAT will cover the cost of her treatment until she is heartworm negative. For information on the heartworm treatment process, visit: onetail.org/heartworm

Mae's adoption fee is 300. She is spayed, up to date on core vaccines, microchipped and heartworm positive.

***We are receiving a much higher than usual number of adoption applications. We ask that you please be patient and someone will be in touch via email within 72 hours. Please do not email us unless you have not received a response in 72 hours. Please only fill out one adoption application. ***

animal.description:
If you are interested in adopting me please go to www.fureverunitedrescue.com to fill out an application. 

I am in a foster home in South Texas, and will be transported to the Pacific Northwest once adopted. 

Blondie is a 7 year old gal that came to us after living much of her life on a chain. She used to be shy and unsure about her surroundings. In her foster home she has really blossomed into a social butterfly. We love to watch her zoom zoom around the yard and roll in the grass. 

Blondie is housebroken, crate trained and walks well on a leash. She is good with children and other big dogs.

TOTAL FEES FOR ADOPTION:   Adoption Fee of $275 + Texas Sales tax of 8.25%  + $150 transport fee for a total due of $447.69. The adoption fee includes all age appropriate vaccinations (spay/neuter, microchip, health certificate) and the transport fee covers transport to the Pacific Northwest on the next available date).

TRANSPORT: Currently we have monthly transports. It will be up to the adoptive family to meet the transport to pick up your new family member. Please be advised that our dogs are adopted to their forever families prior to being transported to the Pacific Northwest. Unfortunately at this time, we cannot bring dogs for a typical meet and greet situation, due to the extensiveness of the transport distance and it being unfair for the dogs who are not adopted to have to make the trip back. 

Due to the number of requests that we receive on our puppies and dogs, please be advised that all adoption applications are processed in the order received. Once we send you an application, your place in line does not get reserved until your application is returned to us.

animal.description: Dimples is an absolute sweetheart who loves to be pet and give hugs, she has been through a lot in her life and is at the point where she deserves a quite place to call her very own. She came to us through a recent rescue effort from an overcrowded and underfunded shelter in Arkansas. In this particular area, when owners no longer want their pets, or a stray dog wonders on your property, you simply shoot it. Thats what happened to Dimples and many of the other dogs we took from this shelter. Thankfully our partner shelter was there to take Dimples in and her many friends that would have been left injured to die. Dimples has come a long way, she made it through this ordeal and many others that she has the scars to prove it, after spending almost two yers in the Arkansas shelter with no adopters coming through, we chose her and hope to be able to make her a Michigander! All she needs now is a place to call her own and be spoiled. We estimate her to be 6 years old, she is heartworm positive and has begun treatment through our shelter. She is a quite, calm and gentle girl that would love nothing more than a couch to lay on and someone to give her constant love! - We would have to cat test her if the adopters have a cat and need to do a dog to dog introduction with the adopters current dogs.

animal.description:
Meeka is a 1-2 year old Shar-Pei mix. Meeka, along with her owner, and three other furry sisters and two other furry brothers, were evicted from their home last October. When asked to help, we made room for all dogs in the home. Meeka came to us pregnant, with puppies due soon. Within weeks of her arrival she gave birth to six beautiful puppies. Her puppies have found their homes and now she is ready for a forever home of her own. Meeka is a very loving, loyal girl. She is a medium sized dog but very sturdy in stature and totally house trained. Once you earn her trust, expect to be showered with kisses and have a rather large lap dog for a pet. Treats and patience are the tickets to getting on the Meeka train. She grew up in a house full of dogs and got along with all of them. We would,however, suggest a meet and greet with any other resident dogs. She has springs on her feet so a physical fence is required. 

AHeinz57 Pet Rescue and Transport is a 501c3 no-kill animal rescue located in De Soto, Iowa. Our pets are located at our facility and in foster homes around Central Iowa. We do adopt to out of town applicants, however we do require new family members be picked up in person. 

If you are interested in meeting one of our adorable adoptables, the first step in our process is to complete an adoption application. To complete an application or read more about our adoption process, please visit our website:

https://www.aheinz57.com/adopt-a-pet/adoption-process/
Our adoption fees are:

$300 - Puppies (up to 6 months)

$195 - Dogs age 6 months - 7 years

$100 - Senior Dogs (age 8 and up)

$200 - Bonded Buddies

$100 - Kittens (up to age 6 months)

$150 - 2 Kittens

$60 - Cats age 6 months and up

$90 - 2 Cats

For the most up-to-date listing of adoptable animals, please visit our website: https://www.aheinz57.com/adopt-a-pet/

Thank you for considering adopting a rescue animal!

Schmidty is an absolute angel with his happy smile and beautiful eyes that beg for your attention. He loves to play fetch in the yard and run around. He has a couple of play mates here that he likes as long as they don't try to go for his ball as he can be protective over his things.

We will be requiring a fenced yard for him as he likes to follow his nose and needs more work on his recall. Additionally, this dog is not meant for apartment life, he needs room and lots of exercise.

He walks the best on leash with a harness and some yummy jerky or pork treats. He doesn't walk nicely if it is just attached to his collar - although some training will help that. 

Schmidty would love to cuddle up next to his owner and receive belly rubs, he is a big snuggle buddy and will keep you warm. With a little more basic training, Schmidty will make anyone a great companion!

Purebred rottweiler female approximately 3 to 4 years old. Sweet personality, likes to cuddle. Healthy, good weight, seems to be good with dogs of all sizes from what we have observed so far. We rescued her from a shelter in las Angelas on 1/18/21. Looking for a home with owners that have time to work on her training, Older kids should be fine. Young kids may be fine too we just have not seen her with toddlers before. She is playful. She is Still a little nervous and unsure of her surroundings since Weinstein got her a couple of days ago. 
 

you must live in Arizona to adopt from us. 
 

Our Adoption Process... If you are interested in adopting one of our fun loving not so rotten rotties, you will be asked to fill out a questionnaire that will allows us to get to know you better and to make sure the dog you are looking at is a good fit for your family and lifestyle. You can access our questionnaire by going to our website, www.rottenrottie.com click on the forms tab, and fill out the questionnaire and submit it online. After we review your answers, if we feel that the dog that you are interested in, is not a good fit for you and your family, we may recommend a different rottweiler companion. After we determine which Rottweiler(s) is the best for you, we will set up a time so that you can meet him or her at their house, where they will feel most comfortable and act as they normally do. An adoption contract will be signed to finalize the adoption and we do ask for a rehoming fee of $400 for most adults, $250 for most of our seniors 6 years and above for any rottweiler mix of any age (except puppies) . Our fees for puppies fluctuate depending on how much we had to invest into them or their litter, and weather they are purebred or a mix. These funds are necessary so that our organization may continue to rehome rottweilers. ALL of our dogs are sterilized, fully vaccinated and microchipped, heartworm tested negative and come with a collar and a leash. We have also addressed any injury or illness that they had when they came to us, or received in foster care. These problems will be disclosed to the adopter prior to adoption.

animal.description:
This beautiful girl is only a year old and has already had a littler of puppies. The person who had her before kept her in an outdoor kennel that was barely 4 x 6 ft so Tanzie had not experienced much in her young life. Fast forward a few weeks later after she has finished raising her puppies and learned how to enjoy all the comforts and love of being a beloved member of a family. She is a happy, easy going girl whose tail wags at the sight of her people and she plays happily with toys and with the other doggies. From the day she arrived she was great with the doggies and even when she had her puppies she was friendly. Best guess on her breed is a shepherd mix of some kinds. She has the most perfect mask on her face and a pretty tan and white coat of medium length - so pretty! This smart girl is completely house trained and taught herself how to use the dog door so she can come and go as she desires. Walking on leash is great fun for this girl and her family wonders if she might have some hound in her as she is constantly sniffing and exploring her environment. Tanzie is a medium girl who weighs about 40 lbs but could stand to gain another 5 lbs. She tested positive for ehrlichia from a tick bite. Treatment is 30 days of antibiotics which will be completed mid February. Tanzie does like to bark at deer and wildlife.

If you are interested in adopting please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $350 includes the spay/neuter, vaccinations, deworming and microchip. 

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.
